<div class="script">New Brides</div>
  <p>1 - If you already have a registry started somewhere else you can simply use the <a href="/getbookmarklet">toolbar button</a> to consolidate your registry into one universal Wedding Registry wishlist!</p>
  <br />
  <p>2 - Once you have the toolbar button, its as easy as simply clicking it when you see a single item on a page that you like. And presto! its in your list!</p>
  <br />
  <p>3 - If you want a set of something or multiple items of the same gift, like stemware or place settings, simply click that button as many times as you want sets. (i.e. 8 place settings: 8 items), allowing people to each select one if desired.</p>
  <br />
  <p>4 - Remember that when you are out and about and see something you like, you can snap it with The Wedding Registry on your smart phone!  It's quick, free, and convenient, you can even add the location and the sales persons name if you like!</p>
  <br />
  <p>5 - Invite your guests early in the process,  many of them may need time to confirm your email invite.  We find that its never too early to let your guests know what you are wanting. With The Wedding Registry you can include things like your honeymoon (for a group purchase)  or even your wedding dress (with store location).  But remember, don’t let him see the picture of it before the big day!</p>
<br />
